14.9. (Well-known problem). Let W∗(Fk) denote the von Neumann algebra of the free group of rank k ∈ {2, 3, . . . , ℵ0}. Is W∗(Fk) isomorphic to W∗(Fl) for k ≠ l?
For a group G, recall that W∗(G) is an appropriate completion of the group algebra CG (see e. g. S. Sakai, C∗-algebras and W∗-algebras, Springer, 1971, in particular Problem 4.4.44). It is known that either W∗(Fk) ∼= W∗(Fl) for all k, l ∈ {2, 3, . . . , ℵ0}, or that the W∗(Fk) are pairwise non-isomorphic (F. Radulescu, Invent. Math., 115 (1994), 347–389, Corollary 4.7).
P. de la Harpe
